pageContext.claim: “AOC, but didn't she steal two million dollars out of her campaign? Didn't AOC steal two million dollars out of her campaign? So why aren't they looking at her? Why aren't they looking at her? Justice Department. The Justice Department they should be looking at -- She stole two million dollars out of her campaign, AOC plus three, right?”
pageContext.analysis: We have no idea what Trump is referring to here. It could be about the fact a limited liability company owned by aide Saikat Chakrabarti, who is now Ocasio-Cortez’s chief of staff, received more than $1 million from two PACs that he co-founded, according to federal campaign finance documents detailing spending from 2016 and 2017. That was described as "weird — and hard to understand why they did it — but probably not unlawful." Or it could be because she raised more than $2 million for her re-election race. Either way, another baseless claim by Trump alleging illegal activities by a Democrat.
